      "content": "Your concern about hitting a low is understandable, but skipping a basal dose can create a false sense of security that leads to a dangerous crash later when your body needs insulin for food digestion. It is safer to keep the basal dose and use a small amount of fast-acting sugar if your blood sugar is low right now. Please consult your doctor or a healthcare professional before making any changes to your insulin regimen.",
